  "bib_entries": {
    "119631785": {
      "title": "Path spaces, continuous tensor products, and E 0 -semigroups",
      "abstract": "We classify all continuous tensor product systems of Hilbert spaces which are “infinitely divisible” in the sense that they have an associated logarithmic structure. These results are applied to the theory of E 0-semigroups to deduce that every E 0-semigroup possessing sufficiently many “decomposable” operators must be cocycle conjugate to a CCR flow (Theorem 12.3)."
